<body>
  <h1>IRC</h1>

  <p>This is an IRC client and server.</p>

  <p><a href="/cgi/start_irc">Show me</a></p>

  <p>The intention is to control all Erlang components with
  IRC</p>

  <p>Erlang components (web-servers, indexing engines, databases etc.)
  should appear to be "chat-rooms" in an IRC interface. To interact
  with <i>mnesia</i> for example, one might say:</p>

  <pre>
    /join #mnesia
  </pre>

  <p>This would enter the chat room mnesia, then you could chat with
  the #mnesia bot:</p>

  <pre>
    joe: show tables
    #mnesia: one two three
    joe: describe one
    #mnesia: {name:string(), ag::integer()}
    ...
  </pre>


 </body>

